<TITLE> Statues for Ctg monasteries </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Jan 30 (bdnews24.com) Communal harmony has been one of the key concerns of the Awami League-led government, says minister Dilip Barua. The minister for industries Friday attended a ceremony here that saw 57 Buddha statues distributed among the monasteries in the Chittagong region. The statues came Siddharth United Social Welfare Mission in India. The distribution marked the 60th birth anniversary of three monks in Chittagong. Mayor A B M Mohiuddin Chowdhury and Buddhist leader Shuddhananda Mahathero were also among the speakers at the ceremony at the city's Polo Ground School. 
